    <text id="B0050T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Annie Branham states that she will wait until her accounts with her servant
                    Joshua are examined by "disinterested persons" before she takes further action,
                    but maintains that she owes him nothing.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                

                <opener>
                    
                    <salute>Mr Jackson</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I did not give Joshua an order &amp; shall not do anything further in the
                    matter until the whole matter is investigated by disinterested persons. My
                    accounts must be examined to see that they are correct. If so--I am not owing
                    Joshua anything--If I choose to give him the board of the boys I can do so, but
                    I will not be forced to support servants and take all their impositions
                    passively.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours Respectfully,</salute>
                    <signed>Annie E. Branham</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">Please send Joshua to me</seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
